#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "thag1.14:4.1"
msgid "1.14. Sivakasāmaṇeragāthā"
msgstr "1.14. The Novice Sivaka"

#. </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a
#. class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc14"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts14"></a>
msgctxt "thag1.14:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Upajjhāyo maṃ <span class=\"var\" title=\"avacāsi (s2, s3, pts1)\" id=\""
"note12\">avaca</span>,"
msgstr "My mentor said to me:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.14:5.2"
msgid ""
"ito <span class=\"var\" title=\"gacchāmi (s2, s3, pts1)\" id=\"note13\""
">gacchāma</span> sīvaka;"
msgstr "“Let’s leave here, Sīvaka.”"

# There's nothing in the text to indicate that this is spoken by Sivaka rather than his upajjhaya. In fact the lack of a close -ti above would indicate that it is still the upajjhaya. However the comm, followed by Norman, says the remainder is spoken by Sivaka.
#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.14:5.3"
msgid "Gāme me vasati kāyo,"
msgstr "My body lives in the village,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.14:5.4"
msgid "araññaṃ me gato mano;"
msgstr "but my mind has gone to the wilderness."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.14:5.5"
msgid "Semānakopi gacchāmi,"
msgstr "I go there even when lying down—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.14:5.6"
msgid "natthi saṅgo vijānatan”ti."
msgstr "you can't tie down those who know."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "thag1.14:6.1"
msgid "…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "thag1.14:6.2"
msgid "Vanavacchassa therassa (siviko) sāmaṇero …."
msgstr ""
